{
  "texts": [
    "Let {X n } be a sequence of independent integer-valued random variables having a common distribution with non-zero variance σ 2 and finite third-order moment.",
    "If the maximum span of X 1 is equal 1, then",
    "In the notation of (21) and (22), Theorem 1 asserts that",
    "The following two claims are direct consequences of (25).",
    "For any y 1 and y 2 satisfying (23) with y 1 ≤ y 2, we have P n (y 1) ≥ P n (y 2) as n → ∞."
  ]
}